Turkey Starts Cyprus Water Pipeline Project, Sabah Reports

-- B y   S t e v e   B r y a n t
-- 
2011-03-08T06:08:06Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-08/turkey-starts-cyprus-water-pipeline-project-sabah-reports.html
Turkish Prime Minister  Recep Tayyip
Erdogan  opened construction of a dam in southern  Turkey  that is
to supply 75 million cubic meters of fresh water a year for
northern Cyprus, Sabah newspaper reported.  The Alakopru dam near Mersin on the Mediterranean coast
will be linked to Cyprus by a pipeline running 80 kilometers (50
miles) under the sea, Erdogan said at a ceremony at the site,
the newspaper said. Turkey aims to finish the project in three
or four years, it said.  Click here for web link  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
